title: Golden to coach Gators on Monday amid inquiry
description: Florida men's basketball coach Todd Golden, who is the subject of an ongoing school inquiry, will remain in charge for Monday's game against Grambling State.
author: Jeff Borzello

title: Chiefs block FG to win 4th game on walk-off play
description: The Chiefs won their fourth game on a walk-off play this season after blocking the Broncos' potental game-winning field goal on Sunday.
author: Adam Teicher

title: Buttler smashes England past Windies in second T20
description: Jos Buttler hits a blistering 83 from 45 balls as England cruise to a seven-wicket win over West Indies in the second T20.

title: Is Premier League title race already down to two teams?
description: Is the Premier League title race down to two teams after just 11 games? BBC Sport looks at the chances of the top four.

title: Parker the preferred opponent to face Dubois next for IBF world title
description: Joseph Parker is the preferred opponent to challenge Daniel Dubois for the IBF world heavyweight title in February.

title: Van Nistelrooy awaiting Man Utd fate after 'special' send-off
description: Ruud van Nistelrooy expects clarity on his future by the end of Monday after his interim reign as Manchester United manager ended with a 3-0 win against Leicester and a "special" Old Trafford send-off.

title: Live updates: Lions, Texans clash in a potential Super Bowl preview
description: Jared Goff leads Detroit into Houston, looking for a seventh consecutive win. On the other side, C.J. Stroud and the Texans want to shake off an ugly loss. Follow all the action.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: NFL commissioner Roger Goodell says league will aim for 8 international games next season
description: The international matchups will include returns to Mexico City and Brazil as well as games in Spain and potentially Ireland.
author: Yahoo Sports
